data.description: This home is one of the largest in the neighborhood with tall ceilings and roomy bedrooms. Granite countertops in the kitchen pop against white cabinets and wainscoting in the dining area. Master suite has a large walk-in closet and is located at the back of the house with remaining two bedrooms upstairs. The landing upstairs is currently a sitting area but can be set up as an office. This home is very efficient and located at the top of a circular drive away from main entrances to the subdivision. A very private, covered porch is the perfect place to sit and relax while listening to birds and watching wildlife.  APPRAISED FOR $203,032 ON 2/13/20. PRICED TO MOVE QUICKLY. OWNERS ARE MOVING CLOSE TO FAMILY. CALL MARK (318-272-9649) OR TERRY (318-286-7736) FOR PRIVATE SHOWING.
data.whatILove: This home offers privacy yet is part of a friendly neighborhood where residents walk their dogs and kids ride their bikes. The view of the hills from the family room is beautiful and the woods in the back create a private sanctuary. The layout is great in that the master suite is away from the other bedrooms. Located in the country so no city taxes. Convenient to downtown and only minutes from the Corvette plant. This home is perfect for a family or a single individual. Low maintenance yard and landscaping.
